messages.content: What was added in Comfyroll Studio version 1.76?
In version 1.76 of Comfyroll Studio, CR VAE Decode, CR Combine Prompt, and CR Diamond Pattern were added.
What was fixed in Comfyroll Studio version 1.75.1?

In version 1.75.1 of Comfyroll Studio, a fix was made for issue 112 CR Text Blacklist, which involved adding handling for blank lines and fixing an issue with finding multiple keywords. Additionally, PR108 addressed a fix for a missing import in nodes_utils_text.py.
What was added in Comfyroll Studio version 1.75?
In version 1.75 of Comfyroll Studio, CR Half Drop Panel was added.
What was fixed in Comfyroll Studio version 1.74.1?
In version 1.74.1 of Comfyroll Studio, the show_help function of CR Thumbnail Preview was fixed.
What updates were made to CR Simple Image Compare in version 1.74?
In version 1.74 of Comfyroll Studio, CR Simple Image Compare was updated to automatically resize the second image if its size differed from the first.
What was added in Comfyroll Studio version 1.74?
In version 1.74 of Comfyroll Studio, CR Aspect Ratio For Print, CR Seamless Checker, and CR Select ISO Size were added.
What was addressed in Comfyroll Studio version 1.73.1?
Comfyroll Studio version 1.73.1 included a fix for issue 104.
What is ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes?
ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes is a collection of custom nodes and plugins that extend the functionality of ComfyUI, a powerful and modular stable diffusion GUI.
What are some of the essential nodes in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes?

Some of the essential nodes in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes include CR Image Output, CR Latent Batch Size, CR Prompt Text, CR Combine Prompt, CR Seed, CR Conditioning Mixer, CR Select Model, and CR VAE Decode.
What are some of the graphics nodes available in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes?

Some of the graphics nodes available in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes include CR Color Tint, CR Halftone Filter, CR Vignette Filter, CR Halftone Grid, CR Color Bars, CR Style Bars, CR Checker Pattern, CR Polygons, CR Color Gradient, CR Radial Gradiant, CR Starburst Lines, CR Starburst Colors, CR Simple Binary Pattern, and CR Binary Pattern.
What are some of the utility nodes available in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes?

Some of the utility nodes available in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes include CR Index, CR Index Increment, CR Index Multiply, CR Index Reset, CR Trigger, CR String To Number, CR String To Combo, CR Float To String, CR Float To Integer, CR Integer To String, and CR String To Boolean.
What are some of the animation nodes available in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes?

Some of the animation nodes available in ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes include CR Simple Schedule, CR Central Schedule, CR Combine Schedules, CR Output Schedule To File, CR Load Schedule From File, CR Schedule Input Switch, CR Simple Value Scheduler, CR Simple Text Scheduler, CR Value Scheduler, and CR Text Scheduler.
How can ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes be installed?
ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes can be installed by cloning the repository in the custom_nodes directory, restarting ComfyUI, or by using ComfyUI Manager or downloading from CivitAI.
What are some of the Comfyroll Workflow Templates that use ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes?

Some of the Comfyroll Workflow Templates that use ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes include Comfyroll Template Workflows, Comfyroll Pro Templates, Comfyroll SDXL Workflow Templates, SDXL Workflow for ComfyUI with Multi-ControlNet, and SDXL and SD1.5 Model Merge Templates for ComfyUI.
